&lt;p&gt;*This post is based on two answers I wrote on Stack Overflow:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://stackoverflow.com/questions/22110482/uses-and-syntax-for-for-each-loop-in-java/22110517#22110517&quot;&gt;Uses and syntax for for-each loop in Java&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://stackoverflow.com/questions/22540025/should-i-use-an-iterator-or-a-forloop-to-iterate/22540191#22540191&quot;&gt;Should I use an Iterator or a forloop to iterate?&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Some more information: &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://stackoverflow.com/questions/2113216/which-is-more-efficient-a-for-each-loop-or-an-iterator&quot;&gt;Which is more efficient, a for-each loop, or an iterator?&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;The full testing class&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I created this compare-the-time-it-takes-to-do-any-two-things class after reading &lt;a href=&quot;https://stackoverflow.com/questions/180158/how-do-i-time-a-methods-execution-in-java&quot;&gt;this question&lt;/a&gt; on Stack Overflow:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;lang-java s-code-block&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;hljs language-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-keyword&quot;&gt;import&lt;/span&gt;  java.text.NumberFormat;
&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-keyword&quot;&gt;import&lt;/span&gt;  java.util.Locale;

&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-comment&quot;&gt;/**
